Autoresearch
Run autonomous benchmark, research, or scientist loops with native benchmark logging tools.

Usage:
$autoresearch init [--open] <request>
$autoresearch start [--mode optimize|research|scientist] [--max-runs <count>] <goal>
$autoresearch <goal>
$autoresearch status
$autoresearch portfolio
$autoresearch discover [focus]
$autoresearch pause
$autoresearch resume
$autoresearch wrap-up
$autoresearch stop
$autoresearch clear

Examples:
$autoresearch init "Create an OCR project with CER < 5% on dataset X"
$autoresearch init --open "Explore OCR approaches with CER < 5% on dataset X"
$autoresearch optimize unit test runtime without changing semantics
$autoresearch start --mode research --max-runs 50 search for better OCR architectures
$autoresearch start --mode scientist --max-runs 50 map promising OCR hypotheses
$autoresearch start --max-runs 50 reduce benchmark wall clock time
$autoresearch wrap-up
